 Is Blind]]''\n| Murray\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Lazy Susan (film)|Lazy Susan]]''\n| Doug\n|\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''The Gettysburg Address''\n| Narrator (voice)\n| Documentary <br/>post-production\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''[[Lou Grant (TV series)|Lou Grant]]''\n| Mike\n| Television debut<br />Episode: \"Generations\"\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[Faerie Tale Theatre]]''\n| Prince Henry\n| Episode: \"[[List of Faerie Tale Theatre episodes|Cinderella]]\"\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[Master Harold...and the Boys (1985 film)|Master Harold...and the Boys]]''\n| Hally Ballard\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1988, 1998\n| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Himself (host)\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[A Life in the Theatre (1993 film)|A Life in the Theatre]]''\n| John\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Frasier]]''\n| Mark (voice)\n| Episode: \"She's the Boss\"\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[The West (1996 film)|The West]]''\n| William Swain (voice)\n| Episode: \"Speck of the Future\"\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[The Music Man (2003 film)|The Music Man]]''\n| Professor Harold Hill\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2008, 2012\n| ''[[30 Rock]]''\n| Cooter Burger\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Cyberchase]]''\n| Max (voice)\n| Episode: \"Father's Day\"\n|-\n| 2010, 2015\n| ''[[Louie (U.S. TV series)|Louie]]''\n| Himself\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Beach Lane''\n| Mike Brennan\n| Pilot\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Adventure Time]]''\n| Dream Warrior (voice)\n| Episode: \"[[Who Would Win]]\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Modern Family]]''\n| Dave\n| Episode: \"[[Mistery Date]]\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Untitled Tad Quill project''\n| Jack Lewis\n| Pilot\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Jim Gaffigan Show]]''\n| Himself\n| Episode: \"Wonderful\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Adventure Time]]''\n| Spirit of the Forest (voice)\n| Episode: \"Flute Spell\"\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[BoJack Horseman]]''\n| Joseph Sugarman (voice)\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[A Christmas Story Live!]]''\n| Narrator\n| Television special\n|-